          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657012940250-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lean beef mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to a ragù-like consistency and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> ragù</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add a pot to a medium heat with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657012943877-x200.jpg",
